    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1962-12-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1962-12-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="223"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d223">
                <head>223. National Security Action Memorandum No. 209<note n="0" type="source"
                        xml:id="d223fn0">Source: Kennedy Library, National Security Files, Meetings
                        and Memoranda Series, Memoranda, <gloss target="#t_NSAM1">NSAM</gloss> 209.
                        Secret. Signed by President <persName corresp="#p_KJF1">Kennedy</persName>.
                        Copies were sent to the Director of Central Intelligence and the Director of
                        the Bureau of the Budget.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian"
                            when="1962-12-10">December 10, 1962</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <list>
                    <head>MEMORANDUM FOR</head>
                    <item>The Secretary of State</item>
                    <item>The Secretary of Defense</item>
                    <item>The Administrator, <gloss target="#t_AID1">AID</gloss>
                    </item>
                </list>
                <list type="subject">
                    <head>SUBJECT</head>
                    <item>Actions on South Asia</item>
                </list>
                <p>I generally approve the courses of action proposed by the <gloss target="#t_NSC1"
                        >NSC</gloss> Subcommittee on South Asia in their memorandum to me of 6
                        December.<note n="1" xml:id="d223fn1">An apparent reference to the
                        memorandum also sent to the <gloss target="#t_NSC1">NSC</gloss> on the same
                        date; see <ref target="#d221fn1">footnote 1, Document 221</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <p>In particular I approve a military aid program for the present emergency phase of
                    up to $60 million, on the assumption that the <gloss target="#t_UK1">UK</gloss>
                    and Commonwealth will provide a like amount. If they prove unwilling to do so, I
                    will reconsider whether to continue with our program in any case.</p>
                <pb facs="0456" n="430" xml:id="pg_430"/>
                <p>I would like the subcommittee to submit as soon as feasible its recommendations
                    on the proposed air defense package, a plan of action to encourage a Kashmir
                    settlement, and its preliminary thinking on assistance to India during the
                    intermediate build-up phase.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="strong">
                            <persName corresp="#p_KJF1">John F. Kennedy</persName>
                        </hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
